    {
      "id": 20,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        -1200,
        400
      ],
      "size": [
        400,
        260
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 13,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "This example demonstrates the disable_thinking option added in this fork.\n\nWithout it, an always-thinking reasoning model (e.g. Qwen3/Qwen3.5-family served via vLLM) spends most of its token budget on an internal <think> pass before answering, e.g. ~72s round trip on a 9B model.\n\nWith disable_thinking=true, the same request completes in ~7s with comparable output quality, because the model is told to skip the thinking pass entirely via chat_template_kwargs."
      ],
      "color": "#335",
      "bgcolor": "#446"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        -700,
        -400
      ],
      "size": [
        420,
        280
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 14,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Set disable_thinking to true (bottom checkbox on this node) when your endpoint/model is an always-thinking reasoning model.\n\nSafe to leave enabled even against non-reasoning models or providers that don't recognize chat_template_kwargs -- it's a silent no-op there.\n\nendpoint here points at a local vLLM instance; swap for your own OpenAI-compatible server (llama.cpp, LM Studio, Ollama, OpenAI cloud, etc)."
      ],
      "color": "#335",
      "bgcolor": "#446"
    }
